        <div>
            <p><strong>Work Experience</strong> <br />2010 - &nbsp;&nbsp;State Secretary, Norwegian Ministry of Defence<br />2009-2010&nbsp;&nbsp;State Secretary, Norwegian Ministry of Health and Care Services<br />2009&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strategic Adviser, the Norwegian Labour Party <br />2007-2009&nbsp;Head of Strategy and Communications, Tromsø 2018 (Olympic campaign)<br />2003-2006&nbsp;Executive Councillor for competence building and development, Troms County <br />2001-2003&nbsp;Head of Communications, TFDS/Hurtigruten<br />2000-2001&nbsp;State Secretary, Norwegian Ministry of Culture<br />1999&nbsp;News editor, Nordlys (regional newspaper)<br />1998-1999&nbsp;Head of Information, Norwegian Centre for Integrated Care and Telemedicin/UNN<br />1996-1998&nbsp;Journalist, Verdens Gang (national newspaper)<br />1992-1996&nbsp;Political Adviser, Norwegian Ministry of Local Government and Regional Development<br />1991&nbsp;Journalist, Dagbladet (national newspaper)<br />1989-1991&nbsp;Political Adviser, the Norwegian Labour Party parliamentary group</p>
<p><strong>Other posts</strong><br />2009-2013&nbsp;Chair of the Board, the Norwegian Arctic Philharmonic Orchestra <br />2006-2010&nbsp;&nbsp;Leader, Troms Labour Party </p>
<p><strong>Other</strong><br />Roger Ingebrigtsen lives in Tromsø. He is married to Lene Hansen and has two children, Anne (1997) and Jens (1999).</p>
